							<p>
								Dr. Renee Treat was named principal for Tison Middle School at tonight’s regular meeting of the WISD Board of Trustees. Dr. Treat holds a Bachelor of Science degree from McMurry University in education, communication, and English; a Master’s in Education from Midwestern State University in educational leadership, and a Doctorate in Education from Abilene Christian University in organizational leadership. <br>From 2006-2016, Dr. Treat served as an assistant principal, principal, and Director of Professional Development in Crowley ISD. Since 2016, she has served as the Director of Organizational Effectiveness at ESC Region 11.
